Problem : Can Place Flowers

Pattern: Greedy

Difficulty: Easy

Time Complexity: O(n)

Space Complexity: O(1)

Key Idea
Traverse each plot in the flowerbed.
Only consider empty plots (0).
Check whether the left and right neighboring plots are empty (or don't exist).
If both sides are empty:
Plant a flower (flowerbed[i] = 1)
Decrement n
If n becomes 0, return true.
After checking all plots, return whether all required flowers were planted.
What I Learned
Handling edge cases using boundary checks.
Applying the Greedy approach by planting flowers whenever it's safe.
Modifying the input array to simplify the solution.
